## Task-start checklist (agents)

1. **Classify task** ‚Äî implementation, review, test-only, docs, release, question.
2. **Identify release phase** per `version-management.mdc` ‚Äî branch, CI track, `version.prerelease`; adapt scope (alpha iteration vs beta freeze vs prod hotfix).
3. **Plan** per `delivery-workflow.mdc` ‚Äî layers, i18n, tests, QA YAML.
4. **Read scoped rules** from the table above if paths will change.
5. **Implement** using `architecture-clean`, `kmp-core`, `ui-ux-compose`, `i18n-multilingual`.
6. **Test** per `qa-testing.mdc` ‚Äî run Gradle tasks before claiming done.
7. **Self-review** per `review-commit.mdc` before PR/commit.
8. **CI/release** per `ci-cd.mdc` when pushing or releasing.

## Task-end checklist (before "done")

- [ ] Layer boundaries respected (no UI in domain/data; no `*Impl` in composables)
- [ ] All new strings in **8** locale `strings.xml` files
- [ ] Journey components / semantic colors (no raw Material forms or one-off hex)
- [ ] **New functionality has unit tests** ‚Äî every new domain method, screen model transition, codec, or repository method has a corresponding `*Test.kt` covering happy path + edge cases (`qa-testing.mdc` coverage table)
- [ ] **Existing tests updated** ‚Äî every test that exercises changed code compiles, passes, and reflects the new behavior; no stale assertions left behind
- [ ] **Fakes kept in sync** ‚Äî all `Fake*` and `Instrumented*Fakes` implement the full current interface; no `TODO()` stubs introduced
- [ ] `:composeApp:testDebugUnitTest` runs green (`BUILD SUCCESSFUL`, zero failures)
- [ ] `:composeApp:compileDebugAndroidTestKotlinAndroid` compiles clean (catches broken fakes before CI)
- [ ] `firebase-appdistribution-testcases.yaml` updated if user-facing flows changed
- [ ] No secrets committed; commit only if user explicitly asked

## Reviews & commits

- **Code review:** Use `review-commit.mdc` priority table (P0 security ‚Üí P4 style).
- **Commits:** Only when user asks; message explains **why**; never skip hooks.
- **PRs:** Test plan required; wait for CI green before merge.

